==English==
===Etymology===
Uncertain, probably from imitative origin.

===Pronunciation===
*Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-æp|-æp]]

===Noun===
{{en-noun-reg}}

#A blow, especially one given with the open hand, or with something broad and flat.
#The sound of such a blow.

====Translations====
'''A blow'''
{{top}}
*Dutch: [[mep]] {{f}}, [[klets]] {{f}}
*Finnish: [[läimäys]], [[läimäytys]], [[läpsäys]], [[läpsy]], [[läpsäytys]]
*French: [[gifle]] (slap on the face) {{f}}, [[fessée]] (a slap on the bum) ''f''
{{mid}}
*Slovene [[klofuta]] {{f}}
{{bottom}}

'''The sound of such a blow'''
{{top}}
*Finnish: [[läpsähdys]], [[läpsäys]], [[räpsähdys]]
{{mid}}
{{bottom}}

===Verb===
{{en-verb|slap|p|ing}}

#To give a slap.
#To cause something to strike soundly.
#To place, to put carelessly.

====Translations====
